<TITLE> New timings 'to ease Dhaka jams' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has ordered fast formulation of an action plan, setting separate schedule for schools, markets, offices and banks, to ease traffic gridlock in capital Dhaka. She gave the directive at a regular cabinet meeting on Monday, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad said. Azad said the prime minister asked offices to not set the temperature of air conditioners below 24 degrees. She told officials to wear shirt and pants instead of suits, the secretary added. Monday's meeting also approved a proposal to sign the Indian Ocean Memorandum of Understanding. He explained: "Countries have to work together to ensure security on water routes and curb marine pollution. Seven countries have already signed the memorandum of understanding." The meeting approved expansion of a Small Enterprise Development Project of Agrani SME Financing Company Ltd, a subsidiary of Agrani Bank Limited. The company will have Tk 500 crore in approved capital and Tk 50 crore paid-up capital. It will have a five-strong board of directors, three of whom will be from the bank and two from outside. The SEDP project is currently providing facilities to farmers of Mymensingh and Faridpur. The prime minister ordered officials to widen the services for people across the country, specially the farmers, Azad said. She also called for low interest rates on the SEDP loans. The meeting also approved a proposal to sign an MoU on education between Bangladesh and the Maldives. "The Maldives wanted teachers from Bangladesh as they are going to build a university. They also want their students to enroll in our country," Azad said. b
